text.section:
In this section, "labor dispute" is to be construed broadly and includes any controversy as to:
Wages, salaries, hours, or other working conditions;
Benefits, including health and welfare, sick leave, insurance, pension, or retirement provisions;
Grievances that arise; or
Collective bargaining agreements, including:
The making or maintaining of any collective bargaining agreement;
The terms to be included in it; or
Its interpretation or application.
